quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  21,1,"Mankind’s reckoning has drawn near, while they are in oblivion, disregarding(it) ."
  21,2,"No fresh reminder comes to them from their Lord but they listen to it playfully,"
  21,3,"their hearts distracted. And secretly did the unjust converse, “Is this anything but a human being like youpl ? Will you go along with sorcery while you see?”"
  21,4,"He said1 , “My Lord knows what is said in the heaven and the earth, for He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing.”"
  21,5,"But they said, “A jumble of dreams; rather, he fabricated it; rather, he is a poet, so let him bring us a sign like those sent to the ancients.”"
  21,6,"None of the towns We annihilated before them had believed. Will they, then, believe?"
  21,7,"And never did We send before yousg but men to whom We reveal1 , so ask the people of the Reminder if youpl do not know."
  21,8,"And never did We make them a mere body1,(ones) who eatpl no food, for never were they immortal."
  21,9,"Then We fulfilled the promise to them, so We saved them together with whomever We will1, and We annihilated the extremists."
  21,10,"Most surely, We have sent down to youpl a Scripture containing your reminder. Do you not reason?"